com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Class FieldListFlags

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec.FieldListFlags

  • public class FieldListFlags
extends java.lang.Object
    Combination of bit values that indicates the presence of optional field list content.
    See Also:
    FieldList

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static int HAS_FIELD_LIST_INFO
      (0x01) Indicates that dictionaryId and fieldListNum members are present, which should be provided as part of the initial refresh message on a stream or on the first refresh message after issuance of a CLEAR_CACHE command.
      static int HAS_SET_DATA
      (0x02) Indicates that the FieldList contains set-defined data.
      static int HAS_SET_ID
      (0x04) Indicates the presence of a setId, used to determine the set definition used for encoding or decoding the set data on this FieldList.
      static int HAS_STANDARD_DATA
      (0x08) Indicates that the FieldList contains standard fieldId-value pair encoded data.
      static int NONE
      (0x00) None of the optional flags are set

      • HAS_SET_DATA

        public static final int HAS_SET_DATA
        (0x02) Indicates that the FieldList contains set-defined data. This value can be set in addition to HAS_STANDARD_DATA if both standard and set-defined data are present in this FieldList. If no entries are present in the FieldList, this flag value should not be set.
